CBS political analyst John Dickerson has been announced as the new host of Face the Nation , taking over from veteran broadcaster Bob Schieffer .
The Chief Political Correspondent of Slate Magazine was announced as new host on the show on Sunday after the 78-year-old announced he would be retiring last week .
He is expected to make his first appearance this summer , and the new job .
Dickerson worked for Time Magazine for 12 years , four of them as White House correspondent .